05/02/2007
TALINN, Estonia -- A two-day conference attended by foreign and defence ministers of the Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- as well as the Baltic states -- Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania -- began in Talinn on Monday (February 5th).
Representatives of the United States and the newest members of NATO's Partnership for Peace programme -- Bosnia and Herzegovina, Montenegro and Serbia -- are also attending the event, titled "Adriatic-Baltic-Atlantic".
The conference is focusing on the conclusions of the NATO summit in October, issues related to regional security, international peacekeeping missions and reform processes in states aspiring to NATO membership.
(Vijesti, HRT, Danas - 05/02/07)
